('chunk_2a446c95dcd9618549','file_c7904436411b2e478c','music.md','1. Subject Overview: Music in MYP Arts','Music sits in the **MYP Arts** subject group. Students learn as **performers, creators, and reflective artists**. They investigate how music works, develop their skills, create and perform music, and evaluate their artistic process and product.','{"subject":2,"overview":1,"music":4,"myp":2,"arts":2,"sits":1,"the":1,"group":1,"students":1,"learn":1,"performers":1,"creators":1,"and":4,"reflective":1,"artists":1,"they":1,"investigate":1,"how":1,"works":1,"develop":1,"their":2,"skills":1,"create":1,"perform":1,"evaluate":1,"artistic":1,"process":1,"product":1}'::jsonb),
('chunk_fc67f9c33281a643ed','file_c7904436411b2e478c','music.md','1.1 The Four MYP Arts Assessment Criteria','Each criterion is marked out of **8** (four achievement bands: 1–2, 3–4, 5–6, 7–8).

| Criterion | Title | In plain language | What a Grade 7 musician does |
|-----------|-------|-------------------|------------------------------|
| **A** | Investigating / Knowing & Understanding | Research and knowledge | Investigates a style/genre, demonstrates knowledge of music elements and vocabulary, and links it to context. |
| **B** | Developing | Skills and planning | Practises and develops vocal/musical skills, plans and refines ideas, shows growth over time. |
| **C** | Creating / Performing | Making and doing | Creates (improvises/arranges) and performs music, applying skills and technique. |
| **D** | Evaluating | Reflection and appraisal | Evaluates own and others'' work against criteria, reflects on progress, sets next-step goals. |

> Note: Different MYP Arts guides phrase Criterion A as "Knowing and understanding" and Criterion C as "Creating/Thinking creatively" or "Performing." For Grade 7 Music at IISH, read A = **Investigating/Knowing**, B = **Developing**, C = **Creating/Performing**, D = **Evaluating**.','{"the":1,"four":2,"myp":2,"arts":2,"assessment":1,"criteria":2,"each":1,"criterion":4,"marked":1,"out":1,"achievement":1,"bands":1,"title":1,"plain":1,"language":1,"what":1,"grade":2,"musician":1,"does":1,"investigating":2,"knowing":3,"understanding":2,"research":1,"and":13,"knowledge":2,"investigates":1,"style":1,"genre":1,"demonstrates":1,"music":3,"elements":1,"vocabulary":1,"links":1,"context":1,"developing":2,"skills":3,"planning":1,"practises":1,"develops":1,"vocal":1,"musical":1,"plans":1,"refines":1,"ideas":1,"shows":1,"growth":1,"over":1,"time":1,"creating":3,"performing":3,"making":1,"doing":1,"creates":1,"improvises":1,"arranges":1,"performs":1,"applying":1,"technique":1,"evaluating":2,"reflection":1,"appraisal":1,"evaluates":1,"own":1,"others":1,"work":1,"against":1,"reflects":1,"progress":1,"sets":1,"next":1,"step":1,"goals":1,"note":1,"different":1,"guides":1,"phrase":1,"thinking":1,"creatively":1,"for":1,"iish":1,"read":1}'::jsonb),
('chunk_a8fd8991bf2e5d1215','file_c7904436411b2e478c','music.md','1.2 Arts Related Concepts','Related concepts are the specialised "lenses" of the Arts. Grade 7 Music draws on:

| Related concept | Meaning in music | Quick example |
|-----------------|------------------|---------------|
| **Expression** | Communicating emotion/ideas through sound | Singing a lullaby gently to convey calm |
| **Interpretation** | The performer''s personal reading of a piece | Two singers phrasing the same folk song differently |
| **Presentation** | How music is shared with an audience | Ensemble posture, entrance, stage presence |
| **Structure** | How music is organised (form, sections) | Verse–chorus–verse in a pop song |
| **Style** | The characteristic "sound" of a genre/era | The swing feel of jazz vs. straight folk |
| **Audience** | Who receives the music and how they respond | Adjusting volume/energy for a school assembly |
| **Role** | The function a musician plays | Melody singer vs. harmony singer vs. soloist |
| **Innovation** | Creating something new/original | Improvising a new melody over a known chord |
| **Boundaries** | Limits explored, stretched, or crossed | Extending vocal range; blending two genres |

